frameDefinitions: A Process of using or modifying is scheduled to be applied to a group or mass.
An Agent or Cause causes a Process or State to continue.
An Item comes to be attached to a Goal, with a Connector forming a bond between the Handle of the Item and the Goal (or some part of it).
A Process comes to an end.
A Money_owner exchanges Sum_1 in the  Source_currency for Sum_2 in the Target_currency at some Exchange_service.
Despite some implication that a State would be interrupted, the Entity remains in the specified State.
frameExamples: Three more cars <t>remain</t> to be fixed.
The goaltenders <t>kept</t> the game going with terrific saves.
According to plan, the front part of the hull quietly <t>attached</t> to the docking gear.
After checking into the Intourist-operated $30-a-day Hotel Zerafshon, we each <t>exchanged</t> $50 for Uzbek currency with a shifty loiterer in the lobby at the rate .
